      "text": "I learnt to ride when I was 11 years old. I spent my 50p a week pocket money on hiring a pony from a local farmer for an hour every Saturday morning. I rode over there on my trusty bike, equipped with a riding hat my dad had found in a ditch, a new crop and the Ladybird “Learn to Ride” book (which I still have today). I handed over the cash, tacked up the pony and went out into the field. Every so often I would stop and get the book out of my pocket to work out what to do next. ",
